		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">14.408-2</ph> Responsible bidder-reasonableness of price.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d846e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d860e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer shall determine that a prospective contractor is responsible (see <xref href="FAR-i1116049.dita#i1116049"
                        base="i1116049"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpartÂ  9.1</xref>) and that the prices offered are reasonable before awarding the contract. The price analysis techniques in <xref href="FAR-i1106135.dita#i1106135"
                        base="i1106135"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.404-1</xref>(b) may be used as guidelines. In each case the determination shall be made in the light of all prevailing circumstances. Particular care must be taken in cases where only a single bid is received.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d860e32" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The price analysis shall consider whether bids are materially unbalanced (see <xref href="FAR-i1106135.dita#i1106135"
                        base="i1106135"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.404-1</xref>(g)).</p>
